The paper deals with communication in ad hoc radio networks, which is a subfield of computer networks and falls under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category. The paper also introduces new algorithms and combinatorial frameworks, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
